<TITLE> Police recover body from Bagerhat river </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, May 18 (bdnews24.com)The police on Monday evening recovered an unidentified body from the Balesshar River of Sharankhola upazila in Bagerhat. The body was sent to Bagerhat Sadr Hospital for autopsy on Tuesday morning. Sharankhola Police Station's sub-inspector Iqbal Hossain said that the villagers informed them of the body and the police recovered the body from the Balesshar River at Chal Rayenda area of the upazila on Monday evening. Hossain said that the legs, hands and eyes of the body were tied. A cement sack filled with mud was tied with the body wearing black trousers and striped navy blue shirt. A member of the village police, Abdul Mannan, filed a murder case against unidentified criminals with the Sharankhola Police Station. The police suspect that the man was killed around 4/5 days ago. bd
